metadata.description: I woke up from a dream and had all the words for this song. From the moment I woke up, I wrote all the words down, picked up a guitar, and all the melodies and chords came out with ease. The song is dedicated to my then 6-year-old son who had a hard time understanding why his mother and I were no longer together.

lyrics.text:
Dear boy
Nothing is quite as it seems
Everything’s more like a dream
And then some day
You find the place
You lived is not what you believed
The world outside
Will take your pride
If you let it
It can hold you just as I do

One day
It’ll all make sense
One day
It’ll all make perfect sense

One way or another
It finds you as it needs to
And I promise it’ll see you just as I do
In perfect time what’s left behind
Will teach you all that you want it to

The wait inside
Never dies
But I’ll be here along with you

One day
It’ll all make sense
One day
It’ll all make perfect sense

metadata.name: Dear Boy #1
metadata.title: Dear Boy
